				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I love the format &#8211; a &#8220;Dear John&#8221; letter is perfect for the 250 word limit, I love using this sort of thing as it allows for economy and adds character immediately.</p>
<p>I was convinced Rose was a person at first, and the letter seemed so harsh as a result, I felt sorry for John. I loved the realisation that Rose is a plant (A rose called &#8220;Rose&#8221; perhaps?) and immediately re-read the whole of it realising it was less cruel as a result! It&#8217;s odd that comparing the old lover to the new seems like such a bitch thing to do while comparing the old lover to a plant just means &#8220;things were really bad between us, we are better off apart&#8221;. </p>
<p>Thank you, you made me smile!</p>
