				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I loved this, it simply worked. The tone is perfect, the carefully-rationalised complaint, the attempt to explain ending a relationship without succumbing to anger. My mental image of Rose was someone middle-aged and comfortable and rather passive ;&gt;. So the revelation was a surprise, and an amusing one &#8211; the plant-revelation sentence is perfect, it breaks out as a suddenly pained complaint on top of all that civilised explanation. </p>
<p>I think other commenters have problems with &#8220;I envy her stamina, because I canâ€™t do the same with you&#8221;, and I do think it suffers from over-compression of ideas and thus jars a little. But it&#8217;s a very minor niggle.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

